# Game Transactions API

## Overview
Track transactions for games played by users.

## Endpoints

GET    /api/GameTransactions
    List all game transactions.
    - Returns: Array of game transaction objects, including winnings (`GameResult`).

GET    /api/GameTransactions/user/{userId}
    List all game transactions for a specific user.
    - Path parameter: userId (int) â€” User identifier.
    - Returns: Array of game transaction objects, including winnings (`GameResult`).

POST   /api/GameTransactions
    Create a new game transaction.
    - Request body: Game transaction object (UserID, GameID, CashAmount, TransactionType, etc.).
    - Returns: Created transaction object, including winnings (`GameResult`).

## Error Responses

- 400: Invalid transaction data.
- 401: Unauthorized.
- 404: User or game not found.
- 500: Server error.

